If you got an iPad for Christmas, here are my top app recommendations, starting with my favorite cozy game, Stardew Valley.
You build up your farm and explore the town. It's so wholesome, but it's also very addicting.
Procreate is the best drawing app. You can make anything from simple doodles to advanced paintings.
You can make your own wallpapers for your iPad and you can even do fun DIYs like these book marks.
GoodNotes is perfect if you wanna get organized for twenty twenty five. You can upload digital planners and journals and take digital notes. Perfect for all of your new years goals.
Along the same lines as Zenia, this is a creative journaling app and it's perfect for people who love bullet journaling or scrap booking.
If you want to read for free on your iPad, I recommend Libby. You just connect your library card and you have access to all of your library's ebooks.
And Flip Clock is just a cute free app, but it also doubles as a timer. The Lake Coloring app is the perfect way to unwind after a stressful day. They have tons of different coloring book options.
And lastly, notion is the perfect way to organize your entire life for twenty twenty five.
You can make templates, purchase templates or use the ones that are within notion. The possibilities for this app are endless. Those are some of my favorites.
